## 3. Relationship to other documents

| Document | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| This EULA | IP, license scope, restrictions (Client ↔ Rightsholder) |
| Service Terms | Tokens, updates, support, refunds, voting, liability |
| Local contract with the Seller | Price, payment, taxes, disputes on the sale |
| CONTRIBUTOR_LICENSE | Author ↔ Contributor only; does not govern the Client |

On commercial terms for paying Licensees, Service Terms prevail (unless the local contract with the Seller improves the Client’s position).  
On copyright and use restrictions, this EULA prevails.  
The local contract shall not weaken EULA IP restrictions except where mandatory law expressly improves the Client’s position.

Sale and modification of the Source Code by third parties are allowed only for parties under [CONTRIBUTOR_LICENSE](legal.en/CONTRIBUTOR_LICENSE.md).

This EULA, as to Client ↔ Rightsholder IP relations, is the entire agreement on that subject and supersedes prior negotiations thereon. Changes to the EULA are made only in writing by the Rightsholder by publishing a new version; for a version already accepted by the Client, EULA IP terms are not worsened retroactively without the Client’s consent, except as required by law.

