## 4. Succession

The Rightsholder may assign in writing to a third party (**Successor**) the exclusive rights in the Source Code and/or other rights described in CONTRIBUTOR_LICENSE.

From the time of notice (https://hb3-accelerator.com and/or in writing), the licensor under this EULA is the person named in the notice, if exclusive rights in the Source Code have been assigned to that person.

---

## 5. Acceptance of the EULA and version fixation

5.1. Acceptance occurs through two linked methods:

1. **Local contract with the Seller.** The Client enters into a purchase / license agreement with an Authorized Contributor (or with the Author in a direct sale). Appendices: this EULA and the Service Terms (or Rightsholder-approved localized versions), stating the EULA **version ID**.

2. **License Token.** Crediting a license token to the Client’s wallet on Sepolia constitutes acceptance of this EULA with the Rightsholder. Date, wallet address, and token amount are recorded on-chain.

5.2. The local contract is the deal with the Seller; the token is acceptance of the EULA with the Rightsholder and binds the license to the wallet.

5.3. The Parties fix the accepted EULA text by one or more of: stating the version ID and date in the local contract; retaining a copy of the file; a cryptographic hash of the EULA text stated in the contract or in a token delivery act. Absent other fixation, the accepted version is the one with ID **EULA-DLE-2026-07-16** in force on the token credit date, unless the contract states otherwise.

---

## 6. Grant of license

6.1. Subject to this EULA and, for paying Licensees, the Service Terms, the Rightsholder grants the Client a non-exclusive, perpetual license to install and use the Software for the Client’s business operations on the Client’s own (Client-controlled) infrastructure.

6.2. The license takes effect upon acceptance under Section 5.

6.3. Packages and token amounts follow the Service Terms (Standard — 1 token; Premium — 10 tokens; one license — one line of business, unless the Service Terms state otherwise).

6.4. After acceptance of this EULA and installation of the instance delivered to the Client, that instance (installed copy, deployment artifacts, and related Client data) and the right to use it are the **Client’s asset**. The Rightsholder **may not unilaterally** revoke the license to use versions already delivered to the Client and may not require return or destruction of such instances except under Section 14 upon the Client’s material breach of this EULA. Copyright in the Source Code remains with the Rightsholder; copyright in Updates remains with the relevant Contributor (Section 10). The Client does not acquire exclusive rights in the Software.

6.5. The perpetual right to use **versions already held by the Client** continues after the end of update obligations under the Service Terms. This EULA does not create an escrow obligation for source code unless separately agreed in writing.

