## 14. Termination

14.1. The Rightsholder **does not terminate** the license on its own initiative (including change of Successor, change of commercial policy, or end of support). The license terminates **only** upon the Client’s material breach of this EULA (in particular Sections 8–10).

14.2. After termination under clause 14.1, the Client shall cease use and destroy copies, except backups required by law.

14.3. Provisions on IP, restrictions, sanctions, data, disclaimer of warranties, liability, injunctive relief, governing law, and disputes survive termination to the extent necessary.

