19.4. Until clauses 19.2–19.3 are completed in a signed copy / local contract (incorporating the EULA), the following applies: law of **England and Wales**; **LCIA** arbitration, one arbitrator, seat London, language English; provided that mandatory Client-protection rules at the Client’s place of incorporation remain to the extent they cannot be waived.

19.5. Applications for injunctive relief under Section 17 may be brought in any competent court where protection is needed, without waiving arbitration on the merits.

